data.title: Tennessee Williams’ brother dead at 89
data.meta_description: BELLEVILLE — A former Metro East federal prosecutor and Illinois gubernatorial hopeful who was the brother of playwright Tennessee Williams has died.
data.text:
BELLEVILLE — A former Metro East federal prosecutor and Illinois gubernatorial hopeful who was the brother of playwright Tennessee Williams has died.

Dakin Williams was 89 when he died Tuesday at a Belleville assisted-living center.

Williams served as an assistant U.S. attorney before entering private practice in Collinsville. He ran unsuccessfully for the Democratic nomination for Illinois governor and for a U.S. Senate seat decades ago.

The funeral Mass will be celebrated at 10 a.m. Tuesday at Saints Peter and Paul Catholic Church in Collinsville. He’ll be buried at Calvary Cemetery in St. Louis.

Tennessee Williams’ successes included “A Streetcar Named Desire” and “The Glass Menagerie.” He died in 1983.
